The Biden-Harris administration met with Lin-Manuel Miranda and the Professional Non-Profit Theater Coalition to discuss the challenges facing the non-profit theater industry and the impact on artist employment and the broader economy. The administration reaffirmed its commitment to promoting the arts and humanities and highlighted its investments in theaters, concert halls, libraries, and other venues. They also discussed the importance of theater for mending the social fabric and civic culture, supporting the economic vitality of urban downtown areas, and creating jobs. The National Endowment for the Arts (NEA) provided an overview of its grant programs, research efforts, and convenings to support the non-profit theater industry and the arts overall. Participants in the meeting included artistic directors from various theaters across the country.